{"word":"ἀρχηγός","slug":"ἀρχηγός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρχηγός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἡγέομαι'><el>ἡγέομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>beginning, originating</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, like <el>ἀρχηγέτης</el>, <i>founder</i>, of a tutelary hero, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a prince, chief</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Simonides Lyricus'>Simon.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a first cause, originator</i>, <el>τοῦ πράγματος</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}